
 Prescriptive analytics seeks to identify optimal interventions for achieving desired outcomes, with causal inference playing a pivotal role in assessing intervention impacts on complex systems. However, existing approaches frequently neglect critical data privacy considerations and provide no means to verify the integrity of their recommendations. These limitations hinder its adoption in high-stakes domains such as healthcare and finance. In this paper, we introduce,
